summary: Honestly as much as I want, and probably what is going to happen, Eve to be on the otherside of the door when Villanelle is so...
body: Honestly as much as I want, and probably what is going to happen, Eve to be on the otherside of the door when Villanelle is so excited and so nervous I also hope she isn’t. I hope Villanelle is expecting Eve and nervous and keeps checking the door everytime she hears someone in the hallway. I hope we get to see this elaborate flower arrangement and wines and such in Villanelle’s room for Eve and she’s so nervous. The scene with Villanelle at the door is simply just her checking for Eve. Time passes and Villanelle knows Eve isn’t coming but she decides maybe she went to the wrong room, so she walks every hallway in the hotel and it takes over an hour and Eve isn’t here and she’s angry. Eve told her she would be here and she’s not here and Villanelle is back in her room and the very expensive flower arrangement is staring her at her and she hates it. So she destroyes it and she breaks the bottles of wine and with it her heart breaks because this was all for Eve and then her phone is ringing, why is it ringing, she wants it to stop ringing and she picks it up to throw it at the wall, but it says Eve Polastri and she freezes. She is so angry at Eve. Yet all anger melts away when she answers the phone because Eve is apologizing and Villanelle can’t even get a word in to be angry because every ounce of anger is melting away with each time Eve says sorry and she mentions she got busy at work with a new assassin and jealousy replaces anger. So she recomposes herself and tells Eve it’s okay and gets off the phone quickly because in Villanelle’s head she’s been assigned a new target and her reward for this one is Eve’s undivided attention.

summary: Do you know if the BBC app or website allows you to watch an episode online the day after it premieres? Sort of how hulu and the...
question: Do you know if the BBC app or website allows you to watch an episode online the day after it premieres? Sort of how hulu and the nbc app does some shows. I live in the states but i dont use cable.
answer:
The episodes will air on BBC America and AMC simultaneously. Then I’m assuming, like last year, they will be made immediately available on those particular websites and apps. I think you need a subscription to access BBC America though :(

I can’t find any official word about Hulu but I think they’ll probably get the whole season some time after it’s completed at the end of May.
